# Design Review Notes

## Input Capacitor Selection
Datasheet requires voltage rating ≥ 1.5 × Vin = 18V minimum.
Selected 25V rating (next standard value above 18V).
RMS current rating must be ≥ ½ load current = 1A minimum.
Selected 220µF/25V low-ESR electrolytic.

Warning per datasheet section 9.2.1.2.5: ceramic capacitors must NOT 
be used for input bypassing on LM2596 — causes severe ringing on VIN pin.
Electrolytic required.

## Output Capacitor Selection
Initially calculated C_out = 10µF using ripple current formula.
Datasheet Table 9-3 recommends 180µF/35V for 5V/2A output at 15V input.
Selected 220µF/35V (nearest standard value, provides additional margin).

Key insight: ESR is the critical parameter for output caps in switching 
regulators, not just capacitance value. Per datasheet section 9.1.3, 
ESR must stay within bounds — too low causes feedback loop oscillation.

## Inductor Selection
Initially calculated L = 33µH.
Datasheet recommends 68µH for our operating conditions.
Selected 68µH/2A — larger value reduces ripple current and improves 
output stability.

## Feedback Resistor Selection (R1, R2)
The LM2596-ADJ output voltage is set by a resistor divider from Vout 
to the FB pin. The FB pin regulates to an internal reference of 1.23V.

Formula from datasheet:
Vout = 1.23 × (1 + R1/R2)

Solving for 5V output:
5 = 1.23 × (1 + R1/R2)
5 / 1.23 = 1 + R1/R2
4.065 = 1 + R1/R2
R1/R2 = 3.065

Fixed R2 = 1kΩ (standard reference value, low enough to ignore 
leakage current but high enough to not waste power)

R1 = 3.065 × 1000 = 3.065kΩ
Nearest standard E96 value = 3.09kΩ

Actual output voltage with R1=3.09kΩ, R2=1kΩ:
Vout = 1.23 × (1 + 3090/1000) = 1.23 × 4.09 = 5.03V

Error = (5.03 - 5.0) / 5.0 = 0.6% — well within ±2% requirement.

Note: R2 connected from FB to GND. R1 connected from Vout to FB.
Both resistors should be 1% tolerance to minimize output voltage error.